data.chText: （皮肤上摩擦或烫起等的）水疱，疱
data.enText: a swelling on the surface of the skin that is filled with liquid and is caused, for example, by rubbing or burning

data.chText: （金属、油漆过的木头或其他表面上的）泡，气泡，水泡
data.enText: a similar swelling, filled with air or liquid, on metal, painted wood or another surface
to form blisters ; to make sth form blisters
His skin was beginning to blister.

data.chText: 她的脸让太阳晒起水疱了。
data.enText: Her face had been blistered by the sun.
when a surface blisters or sth blisters it, it swells and cracks

means: (皮肤上摩擦或烫起等的)水疱
(金属、油漆过的木头或其他表面上的)气泡

tr: (pathology) an elevation of the skin filled with serous fluid
(botany) a swelling on a plant similar to that on the skin
a flaw on a surface resulting when an applied substance does not adhere (as an air bubble in a coat of paint)

example: Her feet blistered during the long hike
the tight shoes and perspiration blistered her feet
The Senator blistered the administration in his speech on Friday

value.def: A blister is a painful swelling on the surface of your skin. Blisters contain a clear liquid and are usually caused by heat or by something repeatedly rubbing your skin.
value.tran: （皮肤上因烫伤或反复摩擦而起的）水疱

value.def: When your skin blisters or when something blisters it, blisters appear on it.

example.ex: The affected skin turns red and may blister...
example.tran: 受感染的皮肤会变红，还有可能起水疱。

example.ex: The sap of this plant blisters the skin.
example.tran: 这种植物的汁液会使皮肤起水疱。
停下来浸洗他们起了水疱的双脚
